Quartet for Two Violins, Viola and Cello, Opus 13

history.p: The string quartet in G minor, Op. 13, is the earliest of Nielsen's four published quartets. It was composed from December 1887 until February 1888. It belongs among the works of his youth including two other complete quartets and some individual movements for string quartet.
